h you don't wish the examiner to <em>read</em>.</div><div style="margin-bottom:3px;">30. You seemed to know about this book, and by inference I thought you had <em>read</em> it.</div></div><!--all结束-->  <!--如果不是仅显示学生,或该页没有学生句子-->  <div id="student" style='display:none;'>  <div>1. Your writing is hard to <em>read</em>.</div><div>2. Only Tommy and I have <em>read</em> the book.</div><div>3. There are a couple more files to <em>read</em> first.</div><div>4. <em>Read</em> the on-screen lyrics and sing along.</div><div>5. Your sister is trying to <em>read</em>;please be quiet for her sake.</div><div>5. Sentencedict.com is a sentence dictionary, on which you can find excellent sentences for a large number of words.</div><div>6. I <em>read</em> about it in the paper.</div><div>7. She listened closely while he <em>read</em> the letter.</div><div>8. <em>Read</em> the small print in your contract to find out exactly what you are insured for.</div><div>9. A man comes to <em>read</em> the gas meter to find out how much gas you have used.</div><div>10. He could barely <em>read</em> and write.</div><div>11. To be honest , it was one of the worst books I've ever <em>read</em>.</div><div>12. I'll vouch for the quality of the report. I <em>read</em> it last night.</div><div>13. This light is too dim to <em>read</em> by.</div><div>14. I can't <em>read</em> the doctor's writing.</div><div>15. We <em>read</em> news in the daily press.</div><div>16. She had <em>read</em> about it in the newspapers .</div><div>17. Have you <em>read</em> this month's 'Physics World'?</div><div>18. In her spare time she <em>read</em> books on cooking.</div><div>19. I <em>read</em> my horoscope most days.</div><div>20. In some countries children don't start learning to <em>read</em> and write until they are six.</div><div>21. I took a book with me to <em>read</em> on the train.</div><div>22. She hadn't <em>read</em> the letter and so was unaware of its contents.</div><div>23. By the time she was eight, she 